# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Your PERSONAL LiteLLM API key — each participant gets their own ($25).
#  Do NOT share it, and do NOT commit it (.env is gitignored).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

LITELLM_API_KEY=sk-your-own-key-here


# HOW TO USE IT  (opencode reads {env:LITELLM_API_KEY} from opencode.json)
#
#  Option A — quickest. Run this in the SAME terminal, then launch opencode:
#
#      export LITELLM_API_KEY=sk-your-own-key-here
#      opencode
#
#  Option B — use this file. opencode does NOT auto-load .env, so source it:
#
#      cp .env.example .env          # then edit .env and paste your key
#      set -a && source .env && set +a
#      opencode
#
#  ⚠️  A new terminal tab/window loses the key — re-run the export there,
#      or you'll get a 401 (opencode does not prompt; an unset key = empty).
